# Python Version and Testing

- The system default `python3` is 3.9.6 which is too old for this project.
- CI runs Python 3.12. Use `python3.13` (available at `/usr/local/bin/python3.13`) to run tests locally.
- Always run tests with: `python3.13 -m pytest tests/ -v`
- Never use bare `python3` or `pytest` directly -- they resolve to 3.9.

# Running Tests

```bash
# Run all tests
python3.13 -m pytest tests/ -v --ignore=tests/test_golden_set.py

# Run specific test file
python3.13 -m pytest tests/test_contact_extraction_utils.py -v

# Install test deps (first time)
python3.13 -m pip install -r requirements-test.txt
```

# Shared Modules

Shared code lives in `gcp/shared/` and is copied to function directories by `scripts/prepare-functions.sh`. After editing any shared module, run `bash scripts/prepare-functions.sh` before running tests.
